# Vercel builds ONLY the Vite frontend (src/ -> dist/). The Express backend (api/) and
# the jobs worker run on Railway, not here. Vercel auto-treats a top-level /api directory
# as Serverless Functions and tries to compile it, which fails on api/config.js's
# process.env.SUPABASE_URL ("Unhandled type: PropertyAccessExpression"). Excluding the
# backend + tooling keeps Vercel to the frontend build, which already passes locally.
api/
tests/
scripts/
*.sql
